comments.comment:
The partner of Shiva, one of the supreme deities of Indian mythology.
She is herself a kindhearted deity who has no affinity for battle of any kind.
She is a Divine Spirit, but has manifested into the world by borrowing the body of the girl to whom she is most closely attuned.

Virtuous, mild-mannered, and versed in all types of housework, she is the ideal young domestic heroine, but who is she really...?

Height/Weight: 156cm, 46kg
Origin: Indian Mythology
Region: India
Alignment: Lawful-Good
Gender: Female
In broader terms, she is the kouhai of light.

In Indian mythology, Pārvatī is the wife of Shiva, the god of creation and destruction.
Pārvatī does not possess any particular domain as a god, and is most commonly treated simply as a goddess wed to Shiva.
However, among Shiva's wives are those seen as goddesses of war. They are Durga and Kali. Both of them possess different Spirit Origins than Pārvatī, but they are all considered to possess the same goddess core.

She is also able to manifest as a Rider, in which case she would borrow the divine cow Nandi as her mount. As Nandi is primarily responsible for a good harvest, it possesses unusually low attack power compared to typical Divine Beasts.

『Trishula Shakti』
Rank: EX
NP Type: Anti-Army
Range: 5-10　 Maximum Targets: 30
Knowing Love and Not Acting on It Is To Be Without It
A limited release of Trishula, a trident that Pārvatī borrowed from Shiva, which itself decided her Class, giving her the right to manifest as a Lancer.
Obviously, she is unable to wield the weapon as effectively as Shiva, but that in return helps her to maintain her foundation as a Servant.

Ash of Kama: EX
Pārvatī is a mild-mannered goddess who is weak in battle.
But that doesn't mean she is faint of heart.
Her feelings for those she loves are stronger than any other god.
For her loved ones, even should it burn her own body to ash, she would tap into and ignite her Divinity to convert it into the power she needs to fight.
Her flame may be brief, but its intensity rivals even the power of Kali, the goddess of destruction and another of Shiva's wives.

It is worth noting that Shiva's feelings are not a factor in this skill. She possesses special characteristics that allow her to intensify her love for someone, even should that loved one elect to ignore her.
Her love may be sincere, but...well, it's pretty heavy, like...on a mythological level.

Grace of a Goddess: A+
A gift from a goddess (Good).
Legend tells of Pārvatī slashing her own throat to provide her blood to a follower dying of thirst.

Core of the Goddess: B
A unique skill that shows she was the perfect goddess from birth. Upholds the absoluteness of the psyche and the physical body. She repels any psychic interference, and her physical body does not age or change, no matter how many calories she ingests. As she is a Pseudo-Servant, its rank is capped at B. But that doesn't matter.
My physique! Won't! Change!

The characteristics of the girl who became a vessel, and the goddess who accepted her light.

She has a kind and tolerant personality. She does not assert herself and is virtuous. She is a talented woman who supports Master from the sidelines.
At least on paper, she sounds like an ideal heroine with high stats, but since she detests anything flashy and chooses safe and steady paths, she's somewhat of a klutz.

But just because she has a genial personality does not make her timid. She is in fact very strong at her core. No matter how much she is tortured, she is never defeated. In a sense, she is the embodiment of strong will and grit.
Because of that, should she ever become truly angry, she would be absolutely terrifying. Pārvatī NEVER forgets a grudge, and always makes sure matters are settled to her satisfaction.

A Pseudo-Servant who is composed only of the innate goodness of the girl who acts as a vessel.
But no matter how much she is called the light, she isn't completely devoid of malevolence. Much as it is possible to taint justice, the vessel's tendency toward being somewhat...yandere... That is, the possibility that she would become dangerous if handled improperly still remains, however faint. 
Having said that, it's worth noting that she doesn't just turn evil whenever she gets mad. She does not, after all, simply abandon her sanity when she suffers because of her close connection with the light.

Since Pārvatī possesses the Divinity of a faultless goddess, her withdrawn personality and shyness are gone, and she is very social.
She may get mad or pouty about little things, but whether a misunderstanding or a mix-up, she still reflects on matters logically, and tends to both forgive the person and apologize herself.

voiceLines.name: During an Event
voiceLines.subtitle:
Oh?
It seems something is happening...

voiceLines.name: Conversation 1
voiceLines.subtitle:
It's not healthy being cooped up in your room.
Would you like to go somewhere together?

voiceLines.name: Conversation 2
voiceLines.subtitle:
This is the first time I've been useful in battle.
Please give me a bunch of orders, Master♪

voiceLines.name: Conversation 3
voiceLines.subtitle:
I think trust is the most important part of a relationship between Master and Servant...
Oh, of course I trust you, Master!

voiceLines.name: Likes
voiceLines.subtitle:
What I like...
Cooking, of course.
Home-cooked meals are a must when it comes to nutrition for your loved ones.

voiceLines.name: Dislikes
voiceLines.subtitle:
What I dislike...
For some reason, I find seaweed repulsive. 
I do not like how it's slimy, flimsy, and salty.
Humanity's enemy: wakame.

voiceLines.name: About the Holy Grail
voiceLines.subtitle:
The Holy Grail? It doesn't seem to concern me much, now...
I can only imagine many peoples' lives have been thrown into turmoil because of it...

voiceLines.name: Bond Level 1
voiceLines.subtitle:
Please do not stare at me so intently...
I'm sorry, I'm just not used to it, I don't know what to do with myself...

voiceLines.name: Bond Level 2
voiceLines.subtitle:
I'm trying my very best, but I am really not that powerful as goddesses go...
So...why are you so kind to me?

voiceLines.name: Bond Level 3
voiceLines.subtitle:
Honestly...
You mustn't do that, Master.
I cannot believe you would do that for anyone...
Oh...r-really? Just for me?
I-I-I...um...
Even if it's just because of a contract we formed for battle, I'm still happy...

voiceLines.name: Bond Level 4
voiceLines.subtitle:
I-I'll just come right out and ask you: Master, am I a burden to you? People say I'm a bit...much, so I just hope I'm not causing trouble for you...
Oh, I don't mean a physical burden... I'm only concerned about the psychological aspect!

voiceLines.name: Bond Level 5
voiceLines.subtitle:
Thank you very much.
I'm so happy you have treated me so well..
I am Pārvatī, as well as the girl whose body is my vessel...
I may be pretty complicated, but with all sincerity, I will stay by your side as your Servant till the very end!

voiceLines.name: Conversation 4
voiceLines.subtitle:
Is that the Mesopotamian goddess Ishtar?
She is so pretty, and I wonder about our connection.
But don't you think she's a bit flashy? Sometimes being too much of a free spirit is a bad thing... (Giggle)

voiceLines.name: Ascension 2
voiceLines.subtitle:
[id 303000_0_G020]Trust is a hard to thing to earn.
[id 303000_0_G021]I will try my very best, so please continue to take good care of me.

voiceLines.name: Ascension 1
voiceLines.subtitle: [id 303000_0_G030]Do you think I've become more like a goddess?

voiceLines.name: Ascension 3
voiceLines.subtitle:
[id 303000_0_G040]What do you think, do I look good?
[id 303000_0_G041]I tried for a modest outfit that won't get dirty even in battle.
[id 303000_0_G042]To be honest, I wanted to wear pink...
[id 303000_0_G043]But I don't think I would look good in pink.

voiceLines.name: Ascension 4
voiceLines.subtitle:
[id 303000_0_G050]To come so far...
[id 303000_0_G051]It's all because of you.
[id 303000_0_G052]Thank you very much!

voiceLines.name: Summon
text:
[r]
I have manifested by borrowing the body of a young maiden.

[r]
Since this is new for me too, will you help me grow alongside you?
voiceLines.subtitle:
Hello, Master of Chaldea.
I am Pārvatī.
I have manifested by borrowing the body of a young maiden.
Since this is new for me too, will you help me grow alongside you?

voiceLines.name: Skill 2
voiceLines.subtitle: I AM a goddess, you know!

voiceLines.name: Battle Start 2
voiceLines.subtitle: But I'm not a god of battle...

voiceLines.name: Victory 1
voiceLines.subtitle: The power of love is victorious!

voiceLines.name: Incapacitated 2
voiceLines.subtitle: Argh...I knew I couldn't do it...

voiceLines.name: Noble Phantasm
voiceLines.subtitle:
[id 303000_0_B050]Feel it...
[id 303000_0_B051]This is my wave of love that reaches the heavens!
[id 303000_0_B052]Trishula Shakti!

voiceLines.name: About Spiritron Dress
voiceLines.overwriteName: About the Spiritron Dress (What the Girl Seeks)
voiceLines.subtitle:
Wearing this outfit and being surrounded by all the hustle and bustle of Chaldea makes me feel like we are at a school.
I've never been to school, though, so I'm basing that more on how my vessel feels.

voiceLines.name: Unlock Wardrobe
voiceLines.subtitle:
[id 303000_11_G060]Wow...even though I'm not used to wearing this, it's very comfortable.
[id 303000_11_G061]Tee hee, what do you think, Master?

voiceLines.name: Extra Attack
voiceLines.subtitle: Do you think you can get away?

voiceLines.name: Battle Start 1
voiceLines.subtitle: I have to get dinner ready...

voiceLines.name: Victory 1
voiceLines.subtitle: Now, if you will excuse me.

voiceLines.subtitle: I understand, Senpai.
